 operating modes wherein it is switched between another partial operating mode and a NAV partial operating mode, wherein in the case of said NAV partial operating mode, at an ignition point (ZZP) a largely homogeneous, lean fuel/exhaust gas/air mixture having a combustion air ratio of &#x3bb;&#x2267;1 is spark ignited in the respective combustion chamber by means of an ignition device, and where a flame front combustion (FFV) initiated by the spark-ignition transitions to a controlled auto-ignition (RZV).</p><p id="p-0002" num="0000">The operational stability of the respective partial operating mode can be improved by variation of the compression ratio &#x3b5;.</p></abstract></us-patent-application>